title: Learn about your taxes
description:
Feeling out of the loop when it comes to taxes? We’ve got you covered, The Canada Revenue Agency has a free online learning tool to get you up to speed! Learn how to file your taxes, what benefits and credits are available to you, and so much more. We’ll also explain how the tax system works and why taxes matter.

Go to https://canada.ca/learn-about-taxes to get started.

title: Learn about your taxes: The one about the TD1 form, part 1
description:
Congratulations on starting your first job or getting a new one! When starting, your employer probably gave you a form called the Personal Tax Credits Return or TD1 form. It’s super important to fill out your TD1 form correctly. Don’t worry, we’ll help you through the process!

Visit canada.ca/learn-about-taxes to access “Learn about your taxes,” our online learning tool for lessons, quizzes, and other helpful resources:

title: Learn about your taxes: The one about the TD1 form, part 2
description:
In this video, we’ll guide you through the process of filling out the form correctly, which is important for your taxes. The first page has sections for tax credits that apply to you, like the basic personal amount and tuition. On the second page, there are additional sections based on your personal situation. Don’t forget to sign and date the form and give it to your employer. This is the second part of our TD1 series, so make sure to watch the first part if you haven’t already. 

Visit canada.ca/learn-about-taxes to access “Learn about your taxes,” our online learning tool for lessons, quizzes, and other helpful resources.

title: Keeping your business on track
description:
Do you own a business that owes taxes to the CRA? This video provides information on what to do if you are in that situation. In cases where your business wants to make a payment, the video lets you know about electronic payment options. If your business can’t pay its taxes in full on filing, the video explains how to work with the CRA to make a payment arrangement. The video also lets you know about the legal and financial consequences if your business does not pay.

If you are a business owner who owes money to the CRA, check out this video and if you need more information go to canada.ca/cra-collections.
